    "164016838283d3a059": {
      "type": "body-text",
      "blocks": {
        "38b8610f-4d84-4fbd-8d59-b6ed1d41aba6": {
          "type": "title",
          "settings": {
            "title": "With conversations of this nature often overwhelming, we look to find hope in the mass of doomsaying and negative noise"
          }
        },
        "08eb3a8d-3b3c-4595-9027-26c6e22e3eab": {
          "type": "body",
          "settings": {
            "body": "<p>As such, we caught up with Gail Galle of Project Everyone. Project Everyone, a United Nations Global Partner seeks to put the power of great communication behind the Global Goals - a framework for positive change more recently referred to as, the world’s to-do list.<\/p><p>Of which, we went deep and honed in on Goal 14 - Life below Water and the enormous and essential role our oceans play in mitigating climate change. In addition, we also spoke about ice water swimming, the earthshot prize, the hot topic of space exploration and other ocean and planet positive projects.<\/p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "38b8610f-4d84-4fbd-8d59-b6ed1d41aba6",
